  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (5be158b 2023-10-02T00:23:45.731792000Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\neth_sendTransaction\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nIn a hardhat project I'm replaying all transactions on a `UniswapV3Pool` block by block against a local anvil node and after about 73k transactions (constructed from the pool's event logs) are replayed the transaction fails with the following error:\r\n```\r\nProviderError: intrinsic gas too low\r\n```\r\n\r\nBelow is the command I'm using to start the anvil node:\r\n```\r\nanvil --prune-history --timestamp 1619820000 --order fifo --code-size-limit 4294967296 -m \"test test test test test test test test test test test junk\" --gas-limit 100000000000 --gas-price 0 --base-fee 0\r\n```\r\n\r\nI've had the `gas-price` and `base-fee` at 1 or omitted from the above command but it made no difference.\r\n\r\nThe FeeData I'm getting back doesn't seem to be changing and is fixed as follows:\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  gasPrice: 1000000000n,\r\n  maxFeePerGas: 1000000000n,\r\n  maxPriorityFeePerGas: 1000000000n\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt fails when trying to replay the `Swap` event(i.e. the 73780 core event) on [this pool](https://etherscan.io/address/0x88e6a0c2ddd26feeb64f039a2c41296fcb3f5640#events) at block 12622017",
